result.formatted_address: Nan Tin Mansion, 37 Kau Yuk Rd, Yuen Long, Hong Kong
result.name: Taiwan Kitchen 台灣麵

reviews.text:
Decent food with the choice to pick two separate dish in one. So very good to try two things for the price of one. Someone said it's overpriced. I guess normally HK$70 per person is enough, tea set is cheaper but not a great selection so normally I order off the main menu. 

The male staff there are very nice and always respectful. The seating is good, you can sit for long time without being kicked out, asked to change table, etc. They also have booths to sit in.  Most restaurants are very tight space so this place is nice for its comfortable seating.

A Taiwanese style low budget restaurant, the menu offers several variations of typical Taiwanese dishes. The food is filling, but I found it a bit bland and flavorless, compared to other Taiwanese restaurants. It is a perfect place to fill your tummy once in a while without expecting a heartfelt culinary experience. 

The staff is somewhat rude. Our waitress ignored everything I said in Cantonese and looked down at me, almost in disdain, and had my wife repeat everything.
Reasonable price
I am not live in tsuen wan
Food is not bad.
